      <h2>The map</h2>
      <p>The city map of Amsterdam was to be the foundation and backdrop of the video. Getting the right map in a workable format and high resolution was crucial for the quality of the final product. The level of detail, labels, colors and file format limits the available choice. After a look at the available options I ended up with a Google Maps extension called
        <a href="https://www.snazzymaps.com" target="_blank">Snazzy Maps</a>. Snazzy maps grants control of the visibility and color of all elements on the map. Downside is the 1000x1000 pixel limit and 10 images a day.</p>

      <p>I started out by giving streets, nature and water a highly contrasting color. By doing this, the elements can be split into separate layers by selecting the colors in Photoshop. I ended up stitching about thirty 1000*1000 pixel images to create the detailed map.</p>

